  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_european_economic_area">European Economic Area</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_european_economic_area">EEA</xref>) was established on 1 January 1994 and includes countries which are not part of the European Union.        </p>
      <p>
On 1 April 2013, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 became responsible for administering the application process for 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 seeking funding for healthcare in other European countries; see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/2013/08/europe-x-border-health/"
               scope="external"
               format="html">European cross border healthcare</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
For a list of 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_european_economic_area">European Economic Area</xref>
 countries relating to 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 and NHS 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_overseas_visitor">Overseas Visitors</xref>
 policy, see the:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <p>
gov.uk website at: 
                          <xref href="https://www.gov.uk/claim-benefits-abroad/where-you-can-claim-benefits"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Claiming benefits if you live, move or travel abroad</xref>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
NHS website at: 
                          <xref href="https://www.nhs.uk/using-the-nhs/healthcare-abroad/healthcare-when-travelling-abroad/travelling-in-the-european-economic-area-eea-and-switzerland/"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Travelling in the European Economic Area (EEA) and Switzerland</xref>.                </p>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
